DynamoDB stream
an ordered flow of information about changes to items in a DynamoDB table
enable a stream on a table - DynamoDB captures information about every modification to data items in the table

whenever an app creates, updates, deletes table items
DynamoDB Streams writes a stream record with the primary key attribute(s) of the items modified
A *stream record* contains information abou tthe data modification to a single item in a Dynamo DB table
can configure the stream so that the stream records capture additional information such as 'before' and 'after' images of modified items

DynamoDB is integrated with lambda so can create 'triggers' - code that automatically respond to events in DynamoDB Streams
can build apps that react to data modifications in DynamoDB via triggers

enable DynamoDB Streams - associate the stream ARN with a lambda function that you write
immediately after an item in the table is modified, a new record appears in the table's strean
Lambda polls the stream and invokes the lambda synchronously when it detects new stream records
Lambda can perform any actions specified, i.e. sending a notification or initiating a workflow

enable Dynamo DB stream
create a Lambda trigger
create IAM role which contains all permissions that lambda function will need at runtime
data from stream record processed by Lambda function - publish message to SNS topic - notify subscribers via email



DynamoDB Streams with Kinesis Adapter is OK, but Streams must be activated manually

DAX improves in-memory read performance, not capture time-ordered sequence of item-level modifications

