relational database needs to be set up and disaster recovery plan to mitigate multi-region failure

requires Recovery Point Objective of 1 second and a Recovert Time Objective of less than one minute

Aurora Global Database:
 - designed for globally distributed apps
 - allow single Aurora database to span multiple AWS regions
 - replicates data with no impact on database performance
 - enables fast local reads with low latency in each region
 - provides disaster recovery from region-wide outages
 - supports storage-based replication that has latency < 1 second
 - in case of outage, secondary regions assigned can be promoted to read-write capabilities in nles thann 1 second
 - RTO less that 1 minute provides strong foundation for global business continuity plan
 
 DynamoDB global tables is NoSQL
 
 MultiAZ RDS with cross region replicas - multi AZ deployment is only applicable inside a single region, not multi-region
 database setup isnot capable of providing RPO of 1 sec and RTO less than 1 minute
 replication of cross-region RDS Read Replica is not as fast compared with Aurora Global Databases
 
